gration.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Spring dependencies**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I need the `spring-context` dependency from Spring Boot. Boot’s autoconfiguration does bring it in, but it might be easier to make a direct call instead. I guess I should evaluate if using the direct call would simplify my configuration or workflow. It's kind of a balancing act between relying on autoconfiguration and managing dependencies myself. So, I'll weigh the benefits of each approach and decide based on the project's needs!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_wcdRWxSn4COLKW6K90n9c6hU|fc_0fa83cc723536fd9016a41b4d4a1048190ae1adf3bd4e90462", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rm tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-flyway/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot_flyway/Spring_boot_flywayTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 844, "output": 1171, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33759, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782691011741, "responseId": "resp_0fa83cc723536fd9016a41b4c487d88190887d30f9c3825fe5"}}
